title: The Football Four Podcast previews college football Week 8
text:
Ohio State quarterback J.T. Barrett is making his first start since Nov. 2014 this weekend at Rutgers. (Photo: James Lang, USA TODAY Sports)
1 CONNECT 26 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE After a discussion of the greatest settings in college football, George Schroeder and Dan Wolken get down to the brass tacks of Week 8 in college football on this episode of The Football Four Podcast.
They discuss J.T. Barrett's ascension to top dog at Ohio State, Utah's underdog status at USC, which team is most likely to bounce back between Texas A&M and Mississippi, and which team needs to win more between Arkansas and Auburn. Plus, they break down two teams — Clemson and Stanford — that look like College Football Playoff contenders.
You can listen or subscribe to the podcast on iTunes or SoundCloud below, as well as on Stitcher . We'd like to hear your comments on any of those platforms, and if you have a college football question you'd like us to discuss on the podcast, email us at footballfour@usatoday.com or follow us on Twitter @TheFootballFour .
